 for the mead the long way up on the counter, she sighs, gives up, and wanders over to drag a chair over next to the stage.  She is even more startled by his sudden Gating away, and mutters darkly under her breath.  With a sigh, she grabs a scroll, a slightly battered quill, and a bottle of ink from her pack.  She unstoppers the cork, spreads out the paper, and begins to write.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't believe that the rangers have ever proclaimed to be like you, Shintou, have they?  Not purely for Evil, that is.  Of course they do not, as beings of the Balance.<br>
<br>
&quot;I too am a seeker of Balance.  Evil and Good are opposites, each equally... well...&quot;  She pauses for a moment, seeking the words that would describe this in the common tongue.  She finally gives up and shrugs.  &quot;Well, for lack of a better phrase, they are neither good nor bad.  Both are needed so that the world continues to function.&quot;  She sighs, fiddling with the end of a long copper braid, and attempts to phrase this correctly.  &quot;You are a being of Evil.  Like Good, you are equally needed as a Paladin who fights for good.  If you were to kill that Paladin, and if all Paladins and other beings of Good were to be wiped out, Evil would overwhelm the world.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, this isn't working.  Hmm...  well, imagine a giant bowl that spins.  It wobbles slightly, sometimes leaning towards the right, sometimes leaning to the left, but always moving.  Sometimes, when Evil prevails, the bowl is tipped.  Just for the sake of argument, imagine the bowl tips to the right.  The spinning slows, the wobbling halts, and all the world is enveloped in the Darkness.  Disease and suffering rules all.  There is no day, no birth, and eventually the Darkness even swallows itself in its search to overwhelm everything.<br>
<br>
&quot;Back to the bowl analogy.  Imagine, this time, that the bowl tips to the left.  Once again, the spinning slows, the wobbling halts, and Light covers everything.  It is always day, birth is eternal, there is no pestilence or hurt.  Plants run rampant in the eternal Summer.  It, in the end, chokes itself in its quest for Good.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now, one last time.  Pretend the bowl -stops-.  It is balanced in the middle; there is no wobbling, no tipping.  If Good and Evil were to end their constant struggle against each other, the world fould fall into stasis.  There would be no birth and no death, no night or day but instead eternal twilight.  Everything is frozen in time when Evil and Good stop fighting.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are a being of Evil, and you fight good by hurting and being cruel to cause hurt and suffering.  You rip apart families, you slaughter children, you care for nothing but yourself and your cause.  This is vital for the Balance, for without those like you it would end.<br>
<br>
&quot;Beings of neutrality, such as Rangers and Druids, fight to maintain this Balance.  If Good is tipping the bowl to the side too deeply, we will fight, as Evil beings, until the Balance stablizes and all is once more in constant, steady combat.  Likewise, if all the world were becoming overwhelmed by Evil, we would join the forces of Good.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing matters but this Balance.  Friends, familes, ties...  all are lesser to this.  If the world were overcome by Good, I would now fight beside the Evil beings, even if it meant killing my own friends.&quot;  Sobered by this grim announcement, she settles back into the chair, then leans forward once more to finish the note.<br>
<br>
&quot;So you have every right to be angry at those who fight for the Balance, because no, we cannot be like you.  We are not, and we never will be.  I am loyal to my God and the Balance alone, and no, I would not battle Karana for any amount of wealth.  What I believe states that it does not matter what we own now, since the world could become awashed in the Storm at any moment, wiping the slate clean and restoring the Balance so that it might begin anew.<br>
<br>
&quot;~Amaeliya&quot;<br>
<br>
She ends her signature with a small flourish, blows on the ink to dry it, and leaves it on the stage in hopes that Shintou will find it.  She stretches out her arms to relax the tightness in them that resulted from the writing, then hops off the chair to attempt climbing back up the stool to get back to her mead. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uamaeliya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaeliya</A> at: 7/30/02 9:11:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=soulous>Soulous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/30/02 9:44:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chaos</span><hr size=1> This is amusing, Soulous thinks to himself. I have never had the pleasure of feeling so many enotions in one place at one time.... Father you would like this I think.... I shall spred your love into the steins of some of these fools.... Soulous lets out a evil giggle and takes another sip of his red wine..... <p>Soulous Plaguebearer
