&quot;Your entire theory is flawed because your kind are all greedy, selfish scum who base your sick idea of &quot;good&quot; and &quot;evil&quot; on what helps allow you to be selfish weaklings and what prevents it. We Iksar are not evil, soft skin. There is nothing evil in what we do. As I said before...since you obviously don't consider the Iksar's, or Cazic-Thule's, standards of right and wrong to be your judging point, you are basing your entire theory on your own, completely wrong and perverse, sense of good and evil. You are just a side, no different then any other.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 8/1/02 1:05:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uamaeliya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaeliya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 3:36:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chaos</span><hr size=1> &quot;Then you say that, when your race was enslaved, that was not evil?  Because, of course, as slaves, you had no rights, no minds, no purpose to exist save but to cater to your master's every whim,&quot; Amaeliya replies calmly, tapping one fingernail softly on her clay mug of mead.<br>
<br>
&quot;So you say that all we softskins are...  what was it... 'greedy, selfish, lying pagans', I believe it was?  Very well.  Riddle me this.  How greedy is the softskin that goes out of his or her way to help others in need?  How greedy is the softskin that gives away weapons and food and armor to those who need it even though said softskin could sell or benifit from that gift themselves?  How selfish is the softskin that does these things?<br>
<br>
&quot;You may say that we have never done these things for your race.  I agree with that - not admit, for there is no guilt on the part of the softskins.  You have not given us any reason to trust you.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do Iksar not insist upon doing 'whatever they want, whenever they want, however they want'?  How is this purely a softskin trait?  You say that we will tear apart the world because we want freedom.  I say that is quite a rediculous way of putting it, since you are thinking only of your race.&quot;  She shakes her head ruefully.  &quot;And you claim that we softskins are selfish.<br>
<br>
&quot;Please, exucse me for just one moment.&quot;  She sets her mead down, hops from the stool, and sudden blue stars and bubbles float around her.  A brief whirlwind, and she is gone.<br>
<br>
After a handful of moments, she pops back into view, clutching a worn book under one arm.  She pulls herself up onto her stool and opens the book into her lap, searching for the right tale.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hope you'll excuse my using the gnomish library to find the history of the Iksar.  If I were to borrow any books from Cabilis, no doubt I should quickly find the book I wished to borrow soaked in my own blood.&quot;  She hits upon the page she wishes to find, and rapidly reads down the hasty-looking writing of the gnomes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah...  I should have done this sooner.&quot;  She closes the book with a small 'thwap' and sets it aside.  &quot;Very well - forgive me my ignorance of Shissar.  So, based on this book, the Shissar were '...devastating and vile, torturing souls for no other reason than their own pleasure and driving the largest slave army ever built to the brink of death and starvation.'  But, of course, as you say, this cannot be evil because it is done to a slave, and slaves have no rights.&quot;  Her tone is laden heavily with sarcasm.<br>
<br>
&quot;Unfortunately, it does not mention in this text as to whether the Shissar were scaled or softskinned.  If they are scaled, then I cannot imagine your grudge against those with supple skin.  If they were softskinned, I cannot understand why you blame an entire type of being for the fault of one race.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am not saying that...  oh, bloody hells.  Here we go with another round of my dispising this language.  I'm not saying that Evil is bad.  It is one end of a spectrum.  Perhaps this is why were cannot agree - you and I have different definitions of the word &quot;evil&quot;, and different affiliations with the terminology.<br>
<br>
&quot;You say that my point of view and my beliefs are 'completely wrong and perverse'.  Why do you expect me to believe you if you, rather selfishly and arrogantly, I might add, believe that you are the master race and that, like slaves, the rest of us in Norrath and Luclin have no purpose to exist save to cater to you as you did once to the Shissar?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 581<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 4:01:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=101.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chaos</span><hr size=1> &quot;If that soft skin who is giving things away is not willing to give up their freedom then they are still just as greedy as ever. The only reason to cling to freedom is because you are selfish. They may be doing a selfless thing, but in the end, their still selfish.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't expect you to do any favors for us Iksar. You are our enemies, and I expect you to act accordingly. I never even hinted that you creatures are selfish for not aiding us Iksar. You creatures are selfish when you interact exclusively with eachother.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;All Iksar are born to their respective caste and spend our entire lives serving the Empire, or they are killed if they refuse. As such, there are no selfish Iksar, we are all fighting for our Empire, our God, and Norrath. What few Iksar who are selfish are not allowed to indulge their desires, as our laws prevent them from doing so and keep them in line. You creatures and your lifestyle breed war, hatred and chaos, and encourage completely selfish behaviour. We Iksar are mostly a unified race, and once we conquer this world, Norrath in it's entirety will be unified through fear, and this weak way of life you creatures have abolished.&quot; <br>
